President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Kansas due to severe storms, flooding, and tornadoes that occurred from June 7 to July 21, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Michael R. Scott has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the area, and additional designations may be made if requested by the State and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.